03/10/2006
WASHINGTON, United States -- President George W. 
Bush reaffirmed US support for Turkey's EU bid and economic reforms, during a meeting with Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan in Washington on Monday (October 2nd). 
At a joint news conference afterwards, the two leaders stressed that their governments are partners and allies in the fight against terrorism and radicalism, though media in Ankara noted there was no specific mention of the Kurdistan Workers' Party.
In other news, EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn is in Ankara, marking Tuesday's first anniversary of the launch of Turkey's accession negotiations with the EU. 
(Milliyet, Radikal, CAN, the Washington Post, the Washington Times, AP - 03/10/06)
